Clinical strategies to reduce diagnostic delay include improved education and awareness of antibody deﬁciencyin both primary and secondary care, patient-centred screen-ing [3], the use of the ‘10 warning signs’ of PID (http://www.info4pi.org) and using computer sorting of diagnosticcodes [4].
